---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";

const meta = {
	title: "Tiny Crimes",
	description:
		"Murder Sudoku: Tiny Crimes — a cozy logic deduction puzzle. Read clues, place suspects, and reveal the killer. Pure logic, fully offline.",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<div class="max-w-2xl">
		<div class="mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
			<img src="/tinyCrimesIcon.png" alt="Tiny Crimes app icon" class="h-20 w-20 rounded-2xl" />
			<div>
				<h1 class="title mb-1 text-3xl">Tiny Crimes</h1>
				<p class="text-gray-500">2026-present</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<section class="mb-8">
			<p class="mb-4">
				Murder Sudoku: Tiny Crimes turns whodunit mysteries into bite-sized logic puzzles. Every
				case is a tiny crime scene — a grid of rooms, a victim, a handful of suspects, and a set of
				clues. Read the clues, place the suspects, and reveal the killer using deduction alone.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-4">
				The rules are simple, the cases are not. No two people can share a row or column, every clue
				is true, and there is exactly one correct solution. When the board is solved, the mystery
				resolves: the suspect left alone with the victim is your culprit. No guessing, no luck — just
				clues, logic, and a quiet little crime waiting to be cracked.
			</p>
			<p>
				Built with Flutter on top of a pure-Dart puzzle engine that generates and verifies every
				case, so each one is guaranteed solvable by reasoning alone. Plays fully offline.
			</p>
		</section>

		<div class="mb-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
			<a
				href="#"
				class="inline-flex cursor-default items-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-accent px-4 py-2 text-bgColor opacity-60"
			>
				<Icon name="fa-brands:google-play" class="h-5 w-5" />
				 Coming Soon
			</a>
		</div>

		<nav aria-label="Tiny Crimes links" class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-2">
			<a href="/apps/tiny-crimes/privacy" class="project-link">Privacy Policy</a>
			<a href="/apps/tiny-crimes/terms" class="project-link">Terms of Use</a>
			<a href="/apps/tiny-crimes/support" class="project-link">Support</a>
		</nav>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
